---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const effective = 'April 24, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of service for nikkyamresh.github.io — governing use of the website and sponsorship of Nikky Amresh's open-source work."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-prose px-4 pb-20 pt-12 sm:px-6 sm:pt-16 lg:px-8">
    <header>
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 font-mono text-sm text-text-subtle">Effective {effective}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="prose prose-invert mt-10">
      <p>
        These Terms of Service (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern your use of
        <strong>nikkyamresh.github.io</strong>
        (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;) and any sponsorship you make to Nikky Amresh
        (&ldquo;I&rdquo;, &ldquo;me&rdquo;, or &ldquo;my&rdquo;) through
        GitHub Sponsors. By using the Site or sponsoring the work, you agree
        to these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>1. About the Site</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is a personal portfolio, writing, and sponsorship page
        operated as an individual by Nikky Amresh, based in Bangalore, India.
        It is not a company. Content on the Site is provided for informational
        purposes only.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Sponsorship</h2>
      <p>
        Sponsorship is a voluntary contribution processed by GitHub Sponsors
        and their payment processor (Stripe). Details of what sponsorship
        supports, and the tiers available, are described on the
        <a href="/sponsor">sponsor page</a>. Sponsorship is not a contract
        for deliverables, a service agreement, or a consulting engagement.
      </p>
      <p>
        Any perks listed for a tier (such as early access to drafts or an
        occasional update email) are offered on a best-effort basis, are not
        guaranteed to be delivered within any timeframe, and may be changed
        or discontinued at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the Site to violate any applicable law or regulation.</li>
        <li>
          Attempt to disrupt, overload, or gain unauthorized access to the
          Site or its infrastructure.
        </li>
        <li>
          Submit fraudulent payment information or attempt payment fraud
          through the sponsorship flow.
        </li>
        <li>
          Use any content from the Site for commercial purposes without
          written permission, except where content is explicitly licensed
          (for example, open-source code linked from the Site, which is
          governed by its own license).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on the Site &mdash; writing, design, code examples, and
        images &mdash; is owned by Nikky Amresh unless attributed otherwise.
        Open-source projects linked from the Site are governed by the
        licenses declared in their respective repositories.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        The Site links to third-party services including GitHub, GitHub
        Sponsors, Stripe, LinkedIn, CTFtime, and others. I am not responsible
        for the content, policies, or practices of third-party services.
        Payments are processed by GitHub Sponsors and Stripe under their own
        terms.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and any sponsorship perks are provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo;
        without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including
        warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or
        non-infringement. Information on the Site may contain inaccuracies
        and is not professional advice.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, in no event shall Nikky
        Amresh be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential,
        or punitive damages arising out of or related to your use of the
        Site or any sponsorship. Total liability for any claim arising out of
        these Terms shall not exceed the amount you have paid in sponsorship
        in the twelve (12) months preceding the claim.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to these Terms</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms may be updated from time to time. The &ldquo;Effective&rdquo;
        date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision.
        Continued use of the Site after changes constitutes acceptance of the
        revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of India. Any disputes shall be
        subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in Bangalore,
        Karnataka, India.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:nikkyamresh8@gmail.com">nikkyamresh8@gmail.com</a>,
        or see the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <a href="/" class="font-mono text-sm text-accent no-underline hover:underline underline-offset-4">
        ← Back to home
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
